UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Javier ROSALES, Defendant-Appellant. No. 10-10624

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Aug. 16, 2011. Nancy E. Larson, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Northern District of Texas, Fort Worth, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Michael Curtis Lowe, Law Offices of Michael Lowe, Dallas, TX, for Defendant-Appellant.

*264Before HIGGINBOTHAM, CLEMENT, and ELROD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The attorney retained to represent Javier Rosales has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967), and United States v. Flores, 632 F.3d 229 (5th Cir.2011). Rosales has filed a response. We have reviewed counsel’s brief and the relevant portions of the record reflected therein, as well as Rosales’s response. We concur with counsel’s assessment that the appeal presents no nonfrivolous issue for appellate review. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
